<doc>
  <member name="D3D12_HEAP_SERIALIZATION_TIER">
    <summary>
      <para>Defines constants that specify heap serialization support.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_HEAP_SERIALIZATION_TIER.D3D12_HEAP_SERIALIZATION_TIER_0 (0)">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates that heap serialization is not supported.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D12_HEAP_SERIALIZATION_TIER.D3D12_HEAP_SERIALIZATION_TIER_10 (10)">
    <summary>
      <para>Indicates that heap serialization is supported. Your application can serialize resource data in heaps through copying APIs such as <see cref="CopyResource" />, without necessarily requiring an explicit <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/using-resource-barriers-to-synchronize-resource-states-in-direct3d-12#implicit-state-transitions">state transition</a> of resources on those heaps.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>